<!doctype html>
<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T008 Custom Work Build</title><style>@page{margin:.6in}body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.45;color:#111827;max-width:8.1in;margin:0 auto;background:#fff}h1{background:#1f2937;color:#fff;padding:16px 18px;border-radius:10px;font-size:22pt;margin:0 0 14px}h2{color:#0f172a;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px;margin:18px 0 8px;font-size:15pt}p{margin:8px 0 12px}ul{margin:8px 0 14px 24px}li{margin:4px 0}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;table-layout:fixed;margin:10px 0 16px}th,td{border:1px solid #b7c3d0;padding:8px 9px;vertical-align:top;word-wrap:break-word}th{background:#dbeafe;color:#0f172a;text-align:left}.meta{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #dbe3ec;border-radius:10px;padding:10px 12px}.visual{text-align:center;margin:12px 0 16px}.visual img{width:100%;max-width:7.15in;height:auto;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:10px}.note{background:#fff7ed;border-left:6px solid #f97316;padding:10px 12px;margin:12px 0 16px;border-radius:6px}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Custom Work Build</h1><p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T008<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repeat job math to version-one internal tracker</p><div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-custom-work-proof.svg" alt="Custom work visual"></div><h2>Customer input</h2><ul><li>Owner repeats the same estimate math for small jobs.</li><li>Inputs: size, material, labor hours, trip cost, options, and notes.</li><li>Problem: quotes depend on memory and old text messages.</li><li>Goal: version-one tracker that works on sample rows.</li></ul><h2>Version-one scope</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:50%"><col style="width:50%"></colgroup><tr><th>Included</th><th>Not included</th></tr><tr><td>Input fields, quote range, assumptions, notes, simple handoff SOP.</td><td>Payment processing, accounting sync, legal contract wording, unlimited revisions.</td></tr><tr><td>Five sample test rows and one owner checklist.</td><td>Full app, customer portal, or automatic invoicing.</td></tr></table><h2>Build logic</h2><table><colgroup><col style="width:28%"><col style="width:36%"><col style="width:36%"></colgroup><tr><th>Input</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Output</th></tr><tr><td>Job size</td><td>Scale material and labor.</td><td>Base range.</td></tr><tr><td>Material group</td><td>Estimate cost category.</td><td>Material allowance.</td></tr><tr><td>Labor hours</td><td>Estimate effort.</td><td>Labor line.</td></tr><tr><td>Options</td><td>Add choices.</td><td>Good / better / best quote.</td></tr></table><div class="note"><b>Definition of done:</b> Version one works on sample rows, has clear boundaries, and gives the owner a repeatable quoting starting point.</div></body></html>